narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: As its title emphasizes, Academic and Professional Spoken Japanese works to bring one's Japanese verbal skills to a higher degree than what is offered in other language courses. The class focused primarily on business spoken Japanese, which was the subcategory to which several students subscribed.
If you're looking to maintain your conversation skills this is a good course for you. If you're looking to make major strides in kanji, reading comprehension, and writing skills, 162/163 are better.
